Edit
Argument of type 'Metadata' is not assignable...
Fixed by ensuring metadata is the second argument in the gRPC call (client.method(request, metadata)).

3. Persistent Timeout Issue
Even after fixing typing:

HTTP /auth/register → gRPC createUser → always times out after 5000ms.

Logs confirm GrpcAuthService starts the call but never gets a response before timeout.

Direct grpcurl call to user-service succeeds instantly.

Strongly suggests an in-process connectivity issue (likely auth-service not actually reaching 50051).

4. Possible Culprit
In dev:

auth-service is not in docker-compose, so it may be trying to reach 127.0.0.1:50051 but actually needs to reach host.docker.internal or user-service:50051 (if running in container).

Env var USER_GRPC_URL exists but might be:

Misconfigured in .env

Not picked up by ClientsModule.registerAsync()

Or overridden by default value.

📌 Current State
All HTTP endpoints in auth-service work up to the point of calling GrpcAuthService.

user-service is healthy — responds to grpcurl locally.

The only failing path is auth-service gRPC client → user-service.